<colophon>
<para>
This is the essential user's guide to the dyne:bolic GNU/Linux
bootable CD distribution. Designed to introduce newbies to approach
the powerful tools and applications offered by the distribution,
covers task by task the various possibilities offered to work with
both audio and video in different ways: playing, recording, editing
and streaming. Coverage expands upon and clarifies existing
documentation for the included softwares, giving a simple introduction
to them and an overview of the main features.
</para>

<para>
Concise, to the point, and extensively indexed, readers will find this
volume packed with informations gathered from not previously available
in any other single reference source.
</para>


</colophon>


